# UI/UX Design Language

This project follows a flat, typography-driven design inspired by the pricing page (`features/pricing/`). When building new pages, follow these conventions.

## Core Principles

1. **Content-first, minimal chrome** — no cards, no shadows, no rounded containers wrapping everything. Let content breathe with whitespace and subtle borders.
2. **Typography as hierarchy** — use font-size, weight, and opacity to create hierarchy instead of boxes and backgrounds.
3. **Monospace for data** — prices, model names, code-like identifiers use `font-mono` + `tabular-nums`.
4. **Layered opacity** — use Tailwind opacity modifiers on semantic colors (`text-muted-foreground/60`, `/40`, `/30`) to create depth without extra colors.
5. **Minimal interactive affordance** — hover states are subtle (`hover:bg-muted/40`), borders appear/change on interaction, no loud colored buttons in content areas.

## Page Layout

```
mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6
```

- Max width `6xl` (1152px), horizontal padding `px-4` mobile / `px-6` desktop.
- Wrap in `<PublicLayout>` + `<PageTransition>`.
- Header: `mb-6 sm:mb-8`, title `text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl`, subtitle `text-muted-foreground mt-1 text-sm`.
- Content sections stacked with `space-y-4`.

## Search Bar Pattern

A full-width input with icon, keyboard shortcut hint, and clear button:

- Container: `relative`
- Icon: `pointer-events-none absolute left-3.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2`, `text-muted-foreground/60`
- Input: `h-10 rounded-lg border`, with layered states:
  - Default: `border-border/60 bg-muted/30`
  - Hover: `hover:border-border hover:bg-muted/50`
  - Focus: `focus:bg-background focus:border-primary/50 focus:ring-primary/20 focus:ring-2`
- Keyboard hint: `<kbd>` styled as `bg-muted rounded border font-mono text-[10px]`
- Support `⌘K` / `Ctrl+K` global shortcut and `Escape` to blur.

## Filter Chips (Popover-based)

Rounded pill buttons that open a searchable command popover:

- Shape: `rounded-full border px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium`
- Inactive: `border-border bg-muted/50 text-muted-foreground`
- Active: `border-foreground/30 bg-foreground/5 text-foreground`
- ChevronDown icon `size-3.5` with `rotate-180` when open
- Popover uses `<Command>` with `<CommandInput>` + `<CommandList>` for search
- Checkmark icon for selected item

## Segmented Control

Inline toggle for binary/multi-option switches:

- Container: `bg-muted/60 inline-flex h-8 rounded-md border p-0.5`
- Active segment: `bg-background text-foreground shadow-sm rounded-[5px]`
- Inactive: `text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground`
- Text: `text-xs font-medium`
- Support icon-only mode with tooltip

## Active Filter Badges

Show applied filters as removable badges:

- Use `<Badge variant="secondary">` with an `<X>` close button
- Badge: `gap-1 py-1 pr-1 pl-2.5 text-xs font-medium`
- Close button: `hover:bg-secondary-foreground/10 rounded-full p-0.5`
- "Clear all" ghost button: `text-muted-foreground h-6 gap-1 px-2 text-xs`

## Result Count

```
<span class="text-foreground font-semibold tabular-nums">{count}</span>
<span class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">{label}</span>
```

## List Row Pattern (for data items)

Full-width clickable rows separated by borders, no card wrapper:

- Container: `overflow-hidden rounded-lg border` (single border wrapping the list)
- Row: `<button>` with `w-full border-b text-left last:border-b-0`
- Hover: `hover:bg-muted/40 transition-colors`, use `group` for child animations
- Inner padding: `px-4 py-3.5 sm:px-5 sm:py-4`
- Layout: `flex items-start gap-3.5 sm:gap-4`

### Row structure (left to right):

1. **Icon** (hidden on mobile): `size-5 shrink-0`, fallback shows first letter in a `bg-muted rounded` square
2. **Content area** (`min-w-0 flex-1`):
   - Title: `font-mono text-sm font-semibold truncate`
   - Metadata line: `text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-0.5`, items separated by `·` (`text-muted-foreground/30`)
   - Description: `text-xs text-muted-foreground/60 line-clamp-1 mt-1`
   - Tags: `mt-1.5 flex flex-wrap gap-1`, each tag `bg-muted text-muted-foreground rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium`
3. **Data column** (`shrink-0 text-right`): label+value pairs, `font-mono text-sm tabular-nums`
4. **Chevron** (hidden on mobile): `text-muted-foreground/20 group-hover:text-muted-foreground/50 size-4`

### Price labels:

```tsx
<div class="flex items-baseline justify-end gap-2">
  <span class="text-[11px] text-muted-foreground/60">{label}</span>
  <span class="font-mono text-sm tabular-nums font-semibold">{value}</span>
</div>
```

Unit suffix: `text-muted-foreground/40 text-[10px]`

## Virtual Scrolling

For lists > 50 items, use `@tanstack/react-virtual`:

- Use `useWindowVirtualizer` for window-level scrolling
- `estimateSize` ~130px per row, `overscan` 5
- Items positioned with `position: absolute` + `translateY`
- Measure elements for dynamic heights (disable in Firefox)

## Loading Skeleton

Match the exact layout of the loaded page:

- Use `<Skeleton>` components with matching dimensions
- Replicate the filter bar shape: rounded-full pills + segmented controls
- For list rows: icon + text blocks + price blocks
- For table: column headers + rows
- Always show 8 list rows or 10 table rows

## Empty State

Centered, dashed-border container:

```
min-h-[320px] rounded-lg border border-dashed
flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center
```

- Icon: `text-muted-foreground/40 size-10 mb-3`
- Title: `text-base font-semibold mb-1`
- Description: `text-sm text-muted-foreground max-w-xs mb-5`
- CTA: `<Button variant="outline" size="sm">`

## Detail Page Pattern

- Back button: `variant="ghost"` with `ArrowLeft`, `text-xs text-muted-foreground mb-4`
- Header: model name in `font-mono text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold` with `<CopyButton>`
- Sections separated by `border-b py-4`
- Section title: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground mb-3`
- Key-value rows: `flex justify-between`, label `text-sm text-muted-foreground`, value `font-mono text-sm`

## Mobile Responsiveness

- Filters collapse into a `<Sheet>` on mobile (`lg:hidden` trigger button)
- Segmented controls hidden on mobile, shown in Sheet's "Display Options" section
- Icons hidden on mobile with `hidden sm:block`
- Force list view on mobile regardless of viewMode setting
- Use `useMediaQuery('(max-width: 640px)')` for mobile detection

## Color Opacity Scale

Use consistent opacity modifiers for text hierarchy:

| Level | Class | Use for |
|-------|-------|---------|
| Primary | `text-foreground` | Titles, values, active states |
| Secondary | `text-muted-foreground` | Labels, metadata, descriptions |
| Tertiary | `text-muted-foreground/60` | Supporting text, secondary labels |
| Quaternary | `text-muted-foreground/40` | Units, hints, disabled text |
| Separator | `text-muted-foreground/30` | Dot separators between metadata |
| Ghost | `text-muted-foreground/20` | Chevrons, very subtle affordances |

